SIMPLE: preacher
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preacher
<hw>Preach"er</hw> <pr>(pr⟦emac⟧ch"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. OF. <ets>preeschierre</ets>, <ets>prescheur</ets>, F.
<ets>pr⟦ecir⟧cheur</ets>, L. <ets>praedicator</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who preaches; one who discourses publicly on religious
subjects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How shall they hear without a <qex>preacher</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Rom. x. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who inculcates anything with
earnestness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No <qex>preacher</qex> is listened to but Time.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Preacher bird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
toucan.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preachership</ent>⟦br⟧
